SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYWednesday 20 April S10 V3 Premier League champions Manchester City are expected to have an easy time of it at home to Brighton tonight but there is a thriller in prospect at Stamford Bridge between Chelsea and Arsenal. More details at www.soccer6.co.za. M1 Celta Vigo vs Getafe: In 21 past clashes between these Spanish clubs, there have been seven wins apiece and seven draws.M2 Chelsea vs Arsenal: Arsenal won away on their last visit to Stamford Bridge at the end of last season. The Gunners have lost their last three games.M3 Everton vs Leicester City: Struggling Everton are unbeaten in their past four meetings with the Foxes with two victories and two draws.M4 Newcastle United vs Crystal Palace: Palace have won on two of their past three visits to St James Park.M5 RB Leipzig vs Union Berlin: German Cup semi-final in Leipzig where Union have lost in all four of their previous visits. Union play at Leipzig in the league as well at the weekend.M6 Stade Brest vs Olympique Lyonnais: Brest have yet to win at home against Lyon, drawing four times and losing once in five past visits.M7 Juventus vs Fiorentina: Juventus won 1-0 away at Fiorentina last month in the first leg of this Coppa Italia tie.M8 Manchester City vs Brighton & Hove Albion: Brighton have upset Arsenal and Tottenham away in their last two matches. City have not won in their past three games.M9 Racing Strasbourg vs Stade Rennes: Strasbourg have not lost in their six previous home matches. Rennes’ loss last Friday at home to Monaco was a blow to their hopes of a top two finish and a place in next season’s Champions League.M10 Osasuna vs Real Madrid: La Liga leaders Real have not lost in their past 15 matches against Osasuna, stretching back to 2011. Suggested permutation:R16.00 1 x 1 x 2,3 x 1 x 1 x 1,2 x 1 x 1 x 2,3 x 3